blocks.name: sprid
blocks.content: Two identical representations of the class of all unordered pairs. (Contributed by AV, 21-Nov-2021.)

blocks.name: elsprel
blocks.content: An unordered pair is an element of all unordered pairs. At least one of the two elements of the unordered pair must be a set. Otherwise, the unordered pair would be the empty set, see ~ prprc , which is not an element of all unordered pairs, see ~ spr0nelg . (Contributed by AV, 21-Nov-2021.)

blocks.name: sprsymrelfo
blocks.content: The mapping ` F ` is a function from the subsets of the set of pairs over a fixed set ` V ` onto the symmetric relations ` R ` on the fixed set ` V ` . (Contributed by AV, 23-Nov-2021.)

blocks.name: sprsymrelf1o
blocks.content: The mapping ` F ` is a bijection between the subsets of the set of pairs over a fixed set ` V ` into the symmetric relations ` R ` on the fixed set ` V ` . (Contributed by AV, 23-Nov-2021.)

thm sprsymrelf1o(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4) {

  mptexg(hs0, c2, universe, copab(s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3))))))
  sprsymrelf1o(s1, s2, s3, hs0, hs1, c0, c1, cmpt(hs0, c2, copab(s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3)))))), c2, c3)

  f1oeq1(cv(s0), cmpt(hs0, c2, copab(s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3)))))), c2, c3)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)

  diff.hs1.c(c1)
  diff.wf1o.s(s0, cmpt(hs0, c2, copab(s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3)))))), c2, c3)
  diff.cmpt.s(s0, hs0, c2, copab(s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3))))))
  diff.copab.s(s0, s2, s3, wrex(hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3)))))
  diff.wrex.s(s0, hs1, cv(hs0), wceq(cv(hs1), cpr(cv(s2), cv(s3))))

blocks.name: sprsymrelen
blocks.content: The class ` P ` of subsets of the set of pairs over a fixed set ` V ` and the class ` R ` of symmetric relations on the fixed set ` V ` are equinumerous. (Contributed by AV, 27-Nov-2021.)
blocks.origin:
thm sprsymrelen(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, c1), wbr(c2, cen, c3))
  -| wceq(c2, cpw(cfv(cspr, c0)))
  -| wceq(c3, crab(s0, cpw(cxp(c0, c0)), wral(s1, c0, wral(s2, c0, wb(wbr(cv(s1), cv(s0), cv(s2)), wbr(cv(s2), cv(s0), cv(s1)))))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c1)
} = {
  sylibr(wcel(c0, c1), wbr(c2, cen, c3), wex(hs0, wf1o(cv(hs0), c2, c3)))
  sprbisymrel(hs0, s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2, c3)
  bren(hs0, c2, c3)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.hs0.s(s2)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.hs0.c(c3)
}
